  <static seed="1477" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalLiteralEquations/LiteralEquation280.pg">
    <statement><p>Solve this equation for <m>A</m>:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ \frac{1}{3A} = \frac{1}{B} }</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="7" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>A = \frac{B}{3}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To solve this equation, we multiple both sides with the common denominator <m>{3AB}</m>:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   \frac{1}{3A} \amp = \frac{1}{B}  \\
   \frac{1}{3A} \cdot 3AB \amp = \frac{1}{B} \cdot 3AB \\
   B \amp = 3A \\
   \frac{B}{3} \amp = \frac{3A}{3} \\
   \frac{B}{3} \amp = A \\
   A \amp = \frac{B}{3}
\end{aligned}
}</m></p>
</solution>
